thread.title: Alan

author: Alan
title: Alan
text: I received two sets PawPaw trees last week and have transplanted them. Time will tell if they succeed due to our local weather and the fact that two where broken in half because they forgot to bind a pole to the root-ball so when the box was thrown on the ground upside-down the trunks would not be subjected to stress and breakage. My only other PawPaw tree was packed this way (from another nursery) and it arrived safely and unharmed. I'm happy with the trees and Willis and hope my trees make it. Therefore, not a perfect score.
